  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Pat the <strong>pork belly </strong>dry with kitchen paper, then<strong> </strong>score the<strong> fatty side </strong>in a criss-cross pattern by drawing a sharp knife through the skin, deep enough to reach the meat below</p><p>Season the skin with<strong> </strong>a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and rub it deep into the criss-cross pattern</p><p>Season the rest of the pork with the <strong>five-spice mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683034894033-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683034894033-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683034894033-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683034894033-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1683034894033-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pork belly</strong>, fat-side down, and cook for 5 min or until golden and crispy, then flip and cook for 2 min on the other side</p><p>Cut 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> pieces of<strong> tin foil</strong> approx. the size of A4 paper</p><p>Lay the <strong>browned pork </strong>(skin-side up), in the middle of the 2 pieces of foil (doubling it up prevents any leakages!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1683034899372-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1683034899372-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1683034899372-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1683034899372-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1683034899372-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Loosely scrunch the edges of the foil around the pork leaving the skin exposed and transfer the parcel<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> to a baking tray</p><p>Pour 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>around the pork</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 45 min or until the pork skin is crisp and the meat is cooked through and tender (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>Thai-style crispy pork belly</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
