      "instruction": "<p>Roll the<strong> lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>soy sauce </strong>to a small bowl with the <strong>fish sauce</strong>, juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span><strong> lime</strong>, <strong>chopped shallot</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>–<strong> </strong>this is your<strong> Nam Jim Jaew</strong></p><p>Toss the<strong> carrot ribbons </strong>in a bowl with most of the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>(save some for garnish!) and the juice of the<strong> remaining lime</strong> – this is your <strong>carrot salad</strong></p>",
